		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have this hunch that if you don't implement all the 2A03 peripherals on the 900kHz timebase, you'll never be able to <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=14319" class="postlink">accurately emulate</a> the DPCM read glitches.<br /><br />Now, whether the documentation should say <em>what the hardware does</em> or <em>what makes sense to an emulator author</em> is a different question... but I'm personally inclined to say that phrasing things so that the most obvious implementation only has a single รท2 clock divider shared between everything would be the better plan.

		

